#. <section class="sutta" id="sn55.41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.41:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 5. Sagāthakapuññābhisandavagga → asaṅkheyyasuttaṃ (bj) | abhisanda 1 or sayhaka 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.41:0.2"
msgid "5. Sagāthakapuññābhisandavagga"
msgstr "5. Overflowing Merit, With Verses"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 41. Paṭhamaabhisandasutta → sagāthapuññābhisandavaggo (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.41:0.3"
msgid "41. Paṭhamaabhisandasutta"
msgstr "41. Overflowing Merit (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.41:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puññābhisandā, kusalābhisandā, sukhassāhārā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing "
"goodness that nurture happiness."

msgctxt "sn55.41:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn55.41:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn55.41:1.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.41:1.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.41:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dhamme … pe …"
msgstr "the teaching …"

msgctxt "sn55.41:2.2"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …."
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.400"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.41:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti "
"akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading "
"to immersion. …"

msgctxt "sn55.41:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.41:3.3"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puññābhisandā, kusalābhisandā, sukhassāhārā."
msgstr ""
"These are the four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that "
"nurture happiness."

# Note that in parallel passages AN uses gahetum here.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.41:4.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi puññābhisandehi kusalābhisandehi samannāgatassa "
"ariyasāvakassa na sukaraṃ puññassa pamāṇaṃ gaṇetuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple has these four kinds of overflowing merit and "
"goodness, it’s not easy to measure how much merit they have by saying that"

msgctxt "sn55.41:4.2"
msgid "‘ettako puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro’ti."
msgstr ""
"this is the extent of their overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that "
"nurtures happiness."

msgctxt "sn55.41:4.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of merit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.41:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde na sukaraṃ udakassa pamāṇaṃ gaṇetuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"It’s like trying to measure how much water is in the ocean. It’s not easy to "
"say"

msgctxt "sn55.41:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘ettakāni udakāḷhakānī’ti vā ‘ettakāni udakāḷhakasatānī’ti vā ‘ettakāni "
"udakāḷhakasahassānī’ti vā ‘ettakāni udakāḷhakasatasahassānī’ti vāti."
msgstr ""
"how many gallons, how many hundreds, thousands, hundreds of thousands of "
"gallons there are."

#. VAR: asaṅkhyeyyo → asaṅkheyyo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.41:5.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāudakakkhandhotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of water."

msgctxt "sn55.41:5.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, imehi catūhi puññābhisandehi kusalābhisandehi "
"samannāgatassa ariyasāvakassa na sukaraṃ puññassa pamāṇaṃ gaṇetuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a noble disciple has these four kinds of overflowing "
"merit and goodness, it’s not easy to measure how much merit they have by "
"saying that"

msgctxt "sn55.41:5.5"
msgid "‘ettako puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro’ti."
msgstr ""
"this is the extent of their overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that "
"nurtures happiness."

msgctxt "sn55.41:5.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of merit.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.41:6.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn55.41:6.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.41:7.1"
msgid "“Mahodadhiṃ aparimitaṃ mahāsaraṃ,"
msgstr "“Hosts of people use the rivers,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:7.2"
msgid "Bahubheravaṃ ratanagaṇānamālayaṃ;"
msgstr "and though the rivers are many,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:7.3"
msgid "Najjo yathā naragaṇasaṅghasevitā,"
msgstr "all reach the great deep, the boundless ocean,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:7.4"
msgid "Puthū savantī upayanti sāgaraṃ."
msgstr "the cruel sea that’s home to precious gems."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.1"
msgid "Evaṃ naraṃ annapānavatthadadaṃ,"
msgstr "So too, when a person gives food, drink, and clothes;"

#. <br>
#. VAR: paccattharaṇassa → seyyānisajjattharaṇassa (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.2"
msgid "Seyyāni paccattharaṇassa dāyakaṃ;"
msgstr "and they’re a giver of beds, seats, and mats—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.3"
msgid "Puññassa dhārā upayanti paṇḍitaṃ,"
msgstr "the streams of merit reach that astute person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.4"
msgid "Najjo yathā vārivahāva sāgaran”ti."
msgstr "as the rivers bring their waters to the sea.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.41:8.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
